<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>152</anchor> <rss>erct-003K.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-003K</addr>  <route>erct-003K.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>15</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Embedding</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003K.agda" type="external">erct-003K.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is called an <em><strong>embedding</strong></em> when for any <tex>x,y:A</tex> the action on identifications <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f } \colon  x=y \to  fx=fy</tex> is <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link>.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>153</anchor> <rss>erct-003L.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>erct-003L</addr>  <route>erct-003L.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000Z.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Z" title="Functions and inverses">Functions and inverses</link> › basic definitions</title> <parent>erct-000Z</parent> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>154</anchor> <rss>erct-001Q.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001Q</addr>  <route>erct-001Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Fiber</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001Q.agda" type="external">erct-001Q.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The <em><strong>fiber</strong></em> of a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> at an element <tex>b:B</tex> is the type consisting of elements <tex>a \colon  A</tex> equipped with identifications <tex>p \colon  fa=b</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>155</anchor> <rss>erct-0014.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0014</addr>  <route>erct-0014.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Homotopy</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0014.agda" type="external">erct-0014.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f , g  \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } Bx</tex> be two dependent functions. A <em><strong>homotopy</strong></em> from <tex>f</tex> to <tex>g</tex>, writing <tex>H \colon  f  \sim  g</tex> is given by a dependent function <tex>H \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } fx=gx</tex>. We shall write <tex>1_{ f } \colon  f  \sim  f</tex> for the <em><strong>identity homotopy</strong></em> on <tex>f</tex> defined by <tex>1_{ f } x: \equiv   \mathsf {refl}</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>156</anchor> <rss>erct-000Y.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000Y</addr>  <route>erct-000Y.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Section-retraction pair</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000Y.agda" type="external">erct-000Y.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>s  \colon  B  \to  A</tex> and <tex>r  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be a pair of maps. A homotopy <tex>h  \colon  r \circ  s  \sim   1_{ B }</tex> exhibits <tex>s</tex> as a <em><strong>section</strong></em> of <tex>r</tex> and <tex>r</tex> as a <em><strong>retraction</strong></em> of <tex>s</tex>. Together, <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( s,r \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> are referred to as a <em><strong>section-retraction pair</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>157</anchor> <rss>erct-0025.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0025</addr>  <route>erct-0025.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Retract</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0025.agda" type="external">erct-0025.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>When <tex>s \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a section of <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex>, we say that <tex>A</tex> is a <em><strong>retract</strong></em> of <tex>B</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>158</anchor> <rss>erct-000U.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000U</addr>  <route>erct-000U.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Biinverse</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000U.agda" type="external">erct-000U.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>biinverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is defined to be a pair of a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> to <tex>f</tex>. We will refer to a function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> equipped with a biinverse as a <em><strong>biinvertible function</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>159</anchor> <rss>erct-000X.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000X</addr>  <route>erct-000X.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Quasi-inverse</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000X.agda" type="external">erct-000X.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>quasi-inverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a function <tex>g  \colon  B  \to  A</tex> equipped with homotopies <tex>\epsilon \colon  f  \circ  g  \sim   1_{ B }</tex> and <tex>\eta \colon  g  \circ  f  \sim 1_{ A }</tex>, rendering <tex>g</tex> simultaneously a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">section</link> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Section-retraction pair">retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex>.</p><p>Although no coherence laws are assumed for <tex>\eta</tex> and <tex>\epsilon</tex>, we shall refer to them respectively as the <em>unit</em> and <em>counit</em> of the quasi-inverse.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>160</anchor> <rss>erct-000W.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000W</addr>  <route>erct-000W.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Inverse</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000W.agda" type="external">erct-000W.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>An <em><strong>inverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is defined to be a <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> equipped with an additional higher coherence <tex>\chi   \colon   \mathsf {act}_{ f } \circ   \eta   \sim   \epsilon \circ  f</tex> in <tex>f \circ  g  \circ  f  \sim  f</tex> relating the (<em>a priori</em> incoherent) unit and the counit of the quasi-inverse. We will refer to a function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> equipped with an inverse as an <em><strong>invertible function</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>161</anchor> <rss>erct-003K.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-003K</addr>  <route>erct-003K.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>2</month> <day>15</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Embedding</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003K.agda" type="external">erct-003K.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is called an <em><strong>embedding</strong></em> when for any <tex>x,y:A</tex> the action on identifications <tex>\mathsf {act}_{ f } \colon  x=y \to  fx=fy</tex> is <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000W" title="Inverse">invertible</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>162</anchor> <rss>erct-000V.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000V</addr>  <route>erct-000V.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Equivalence of types</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000V.agda" type="external">erct-000V.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>An <em><strong>equivalence</strong></em> from <tex>A</tex> to <tex>B</tex> is defined to be a function <tex>A  \to  B</tex> equipped with a  <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinverse</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>163</anchor> <rss>erct-000W.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000W</addr>  <route>erct-000W.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Inverse</title>  <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000W.agda" type="external">erct-000W.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>An <em><strong>inverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is defined to be a <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000X" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> equipped with an additional higher coherence <tex>\chi   \colon   \mathsf {act}_{ f } \circ   \eta   \sim   \epsilon \circ  f</tex> in <tex>f \circ  g  \circ  f  \sim  f</tex> relating the (<em>a priori</em> incoherent) unit and the counit of the quasi-inverse. We will refer to a function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> equipped with an inverse as an <em><strong>invertible function</strong></em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks/> <references/></backmatter></tree>